PERFORMACE PROBLEM
--------------------------------------------------------------------
1. Every performance problem is the RESULT OF A QUEUE BUILDING SOMEWERE...
    > Network socket queue 
    > DB IO queue 
    > OS run queue(thread, CPU availible etc.) 

--------------------------------------------------------------------
2. reason for queue build-up 
    > Inefficient slow processing
    > Serial resouce access
    > Limited resouce capacity  

--------------------------------------------------------------------
3. capacity principles
    > Efficiency
    > concurruncy
    > capacity

--------------------------------------------------------------------
4. Types of latency & solutions

    > 1. Serial Request Latency
    - Delay in processing a single request

        > Network Latency
            - Time taken to transfer data over the network
            - Causes:
                * Large payload size
                * New connection setup
                * SSL/TLS handshake
            - Solutions:
                * Data format optimization & compression
                * Persistent connections (Keep-Alive)
                * Connection pooling
                * Session/Data caching
                * SSL session caching

        > Memory Latency
            - Delay due to inefficient memory usage
            - Causes:
                * Memory bloat
                * Frequent garbage collection
                * Large objects in memory
            - Solutions:
                * Avoid memory bloat
                * Weak/Soft references
                * Multiple smaller processes
                * Efficient GC algorithms 

        > Disk Latency
            - Delay while reading/writing data from storage
            - Causes:
                * Slow HDD
                * Frequent disk access
                * Large DB operations
            - Solutions:
                * Caching
                * SSD storage
                * Asynchronous I/O
                * DB optimization
                * Batch writes

        > CPU Latency
            - Delay due to CPU processing workload
            - Causes:
                * Heavy computations
                * CPU-intensive tasks
                * Inefficient thread usage
            - Solutions:
                * Batch/Async I/O
                * Single-threaded event-driven model
                * Thread pool tuning
                * Multi-process in virtual/containerized environments


    > 2. Concurrent Request Latency
        > Contention
            - Multiple requests fighting for the same resource
            - Examples:
                * DB connections
                * CPU cores
                * Memory
                * Lock contention (same DB row/resource)
            - Solution:
                * Connection pooling
                * Reduce lock time
                * Partitioning/Sharding
                * Scale resources

        > Coherence (Consistency Issues)
            - Data mismatch between servers/replicas
            - Example:
                Server A = ₹900
                Server B = ₹1000 
            - Solution:
                * Replication sync
                * Consistency protocols

        > Queueing Delay
            - Requests waiting in line before processing
            - Example:
                100 requests, only 10 DB connections
            - Solution:
                * Increase capacity
                * Better load balancing
                * Async processing

        > Context Switching
            - CPU switches between multiple tasks/processes
            - Too much switching adds overhead
            - Solution:
                * Optimal thread count
                * Multi-process architecture
                * Reduce unnecessary threads
                
